text: Klyuchevoy () is a rural locality (a village) in Abdullinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 180 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 20 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye, 7 km from Abdullino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Klyuchevoy, Republic of Bashkortostan
